64 lies in F2_S2_Office? F2_S2 is 4.11-5.31, so 4.11–4.64 is within F2_S2. So we need to split F1_SW_Lobby_Ceiling into three pieces: 0.00-4.11 pairs with F2_S1_Floor, 4.11-4.64 pairs with F2_S2_Floor. Actually F1_SW_Lobby_Ceiling x-range 0-4.64. F2 south zones: S1 0-4.11, S2 4.11-5.31. So split: piece 0.00-4.11 → F2_S1_Office_Floor; piece 4.11-4.64 → F2_S2_Office_Floor.\n- F1_SM_Office_Ceiling, x 4.64–11.36  ⟺  split into: 4.64-5.31 → F2_S2_Office_Floor; 5.31-10.89 → F2_S3_Office_Floor; 10.89-11.36 → F2_S4_Office_Floor.\n- F1_SE_Office_Ceiling, x 11.36–15.00  ⟺  11.36-15.00 → F2_S4_Office_Floor.\n\nNorth band (y 5.00–8.00):\n- F1_NW_Office_Ceiling, x 0.00–4.94  ⟺  F2_N1_Meeting_Floor (0.00–7.50) covers this entirely → one piece 0.00–4.94 pairs with F2_N1_Meeting_Floor.\n- F1_NM_Office_Ceiling, x 4.94–11.12  ⟺  split: 4.94–7.50 → F2_N1_Meeting_Floor; 7.50–11.12 → F2_N2_Meeting_Floor.\n- F1_NE_Office_Ceiling, x 11.12–15.00  ⟺  11.12–15.00 → F2_N2_Meeting_Floor.\n\nCorridor band (y 3.00–5.00):\n- F1_Corridor_Ceiling, x 0.00–15.00  ⟺  F2_Corridor_Floor (0.00–15.00), no split needed. Full pairing.\n\nExpress each piece as a separate interzone surface; all interzone pieces use Cons_InterFloor. The exact pairings will be enumerated in the IDF by the surface subagent using the split ranges defined here.",
